{
  "texts": [
    "In Equation ( 7), as FN →0, Recall →1.",
    "For GiBy, as more training data is available, its FP →0 and Precision →1.",
    "Since there are no FNs in GiBy, its Recall = 1.",
    "This implies, an extensively trained GiBy that has seen most boundaries will have Precision ≈ 1 and Recall =1, resulting in a F1-score close to 1; w.r.t.",
    "the TP, FP and FN the operator sees.Accuracy = T P + T N T P + T N + FP + FN(8)F1 -score = 2 • Precision • Recall Precision + Recall(9)When FP → 0 (as is the case for it to be practically useful for the operator), its precision is also dominated by the TP."
  ]
}